SIMPLE: twiddle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twiddle
<hw>Twid"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Probably of
imitative origin. Cf. <er>Tweedle</er>.]</ety> <def>To touch lightly, or
play with; to tweedle; to twirl; <as>as, to <ex>twiddle</ex> one's
thumbs; to <ex>twiddle</ex> a watch key.</as></def> <altsp>[Written also
<ex>twidle</ex>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twiddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twiddle
<hw>Twid"dle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To play with anything; hence,
to be busy about trifles.</def> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twiddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twiddle
<hw>Twid"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A slight
twist with the fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pimple.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twifallow</ent>⟦br⟧
